OL,3,CLabour abandon plans for day-one
OL,4,Cworkers' protection against unfair
OL,5,Cdismissal
OL,7,FBusiness Secretary Peter Kyle had
OL,8,Fhinted at concessions over the
OL,9,Fgovernment's workers' rights package.
OL,11,FMinisters have abandoned plans to give
OL,12,Fworkers day-one protection against
OL,13,Funfair dismissal in a bid to ensure
OL,14,Fthe Government's Employment Rights
OL,15,FBill makes it through Parliament.
OL,17,FPeople will need to have six months of
OL,18,Fservice to claim unfair dismissal
OL,19,Fagainst their employer, in a watering
OL,20,Fdown of the legislation and a breach
OL,21,Fof Labour's manifesto.
